The paper discusses the security vulnerabilities of DNS glue, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper analyzes the availability implications of glue, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses limitations of current countermeasures, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of DNS glue, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses measurements of glue redundancies and vulnerabilities, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
